I"y<p><em>Lately I’ve realized a major crisis affecting my ability to make art and take up space in the world is the feeling that as a mixed person, I culturally don’t exist. This felt like a major roadblock, until the movie “The Watermelon Woman” introduced me to the idea that you can write your own history. Then I rembered my friend Sen had participated in a workshop where they explored just this topic. I called them up back in August and asked them a bunch of questions about it!</em>
